2015年4月22日，電影在{{Tsl|en|CinemaCon}}會上舉行了一場預映，並屢獲觀眾的佳評；他們讚賞電影高明的故事情節，然而也有人擔心電影的概念對年幼的觀眾來說過於複雜，而難以吸引廣大的家庭市場。<ref>{{en}}{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/cinemacon-pixars-inside-premieres-theater-790788|title=CinemaCon: Pixar's 'Inside Out' Premieres for Theater Owners|author=Pamela McClintock|work=[[The_Hollywood_Reporter|The Hollywood Reporter]]|publisher=[[Prometheus_Global_Media|Prometheus Global Media]]|date=2015-04-22|accessdate=2015-04-23|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150424225017/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/cinemacon-pixars-inside-premieres-theater-790788|archivedate=2015-04-24}}</ref><ref>{{en}}{{cite web|url=http://variety.com/2015/film/news/pixar-inside-out-premiere-review-cinemacon-1201477371/|title=Pixar's 'Inside Out' Debuts to Emotional Crowd at CinemaCon|author=Dave McNarry|work=[[綜藝_(雜誌)|Variety]]|publisher={{tsl|en|Penske Media Corporation|潘斯奇媒體公司|Penske Media Corporation}}|date=2015-04-22|accessdate=2015-04-23|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150424072042/http://variety.com/2015/film/news/pixar-inside-out-premiere-review-cinemacon-1201477371/|archivedate=2015-04-24}}</ref>電影在2015年的坎城影展舉行首映後，許多影評亦對本片讚譽有加。《[[綜藝_(雜誌)|綜藝]]》的彼得·迪布吉（Peter Debruge）對電影的感情溢於言表，並稱它是皮克斯有史以來「最棒的點子」、以及「一個令人讚嘆的原創構想，…絕對能讓人們永遠地對於『人們如何思考』的想像完全改觀。」<ref name="v">{{en}}{{cite news|url=http://variety.com/2015/film/festivals/inside-out-review-disney-pixar-cannes-1201499227/|title=Cannes Film Review: 'Inside Out'|work=[[綜藝_(雜誌)|Variety]]|publisher={{tsl|en|Penske Media Corporation|潘斯奇媒體公司|Penske Media Corporation}}|author=Peter Debruge|date=2015-05-18|accessdate=2015-05-18|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150518192556/http://variety.com/2015/film/festivals/inside-out-review-disney-pixar-cannes-1201499227/|archivedate=2015-05-18}}</ref>《[[芝加哥論壇報|芝加哥論壇報]]》的{{Tsl|en|Michael Phillips|麥克爾·菲利浦斯}}認為本片是皮克斯繼《[[天外奇蹟|天外奇蹟]]》（亦由[[彼特·達克特|彼特·達克特]]執導）以來最傑出的作品，並稱它「將近期股東操控下劣片百出的歪風給矯邪歸正，實為一部激勵人心、且從頭到尾都十分創新的佳作」。<ref name="ct">{{en}}{{cite news|url=http://www.chicagotribune.com/entertainment/movies/ct-pixars-inside-out-triumphs-at-cannes-20150518-column.html|title=Cannes 2015: Disney/Pixar's 'Inside Out' a return to form|work=[[Chicago_Tribune|Chicago Tribune]]|author=Michael Phillips|date=2015-05-18|accessdate=2015-05-18|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150520090226/http://www.chicagotribune.com/entertainment/movies/ct-pixars-inside-out-triumphs-at-cannes-20150518-column.html|archivedate=2015-05-20}}</ref>《[[荷里活報道|好萊塢報導]]》的托德·麥卡錫（Todd McCarthy）認為本片的想法十分「大膽」，堪稱是所有家庭電影中「最讓人迷幻的構想」之一。<ref name="THRReview">{{en}}{{cite news|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/movie/inside-0/review/796483|title='Inside Out': Cannes Review|work=[[The_Hollywood_Reporter|The Hollywood Reporter]]|publisher=[[Prometheus_Global_Media|Prometheus Global Media]]|author=Todd McCarthy|date=2015-05-18|accessdate=2015-05-18|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150520220855/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/movie/inside-0/review/796483|archivedate=2015-05-20}}</ref>《[[名利场_(杂志)|浮華世界]]》的理查·勞森（Richard Lawson）則寫道：「我認為較年幼的孩子們或許難以完全和《腦筋急轉彎》產生連結，然而它卻很可能讓大人們流下不少眼淚。」<ref name="vf">{{en}}{{cite news|url=http://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/2015/05/inside-out-review|title=Pixar's Inside Out Revels in the Wonder, and Sadness, of Being Alive|work=[[浮華世界|Vanity Fair]]|author=Richard Lawson|date=2015-05-18|accessdate=2015-05-18|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150520225847/http://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/2015/05/inside-out-review|archivedate=2015-05-20}}</ref>《[[衛報|衛報]]》的{{Tsl|en|Peter Bradshaw|彼得·布拉德肖}}認為電影有著「輕盈而甜蜜」的質感，不過相較於皮克斯最好的作品則仍略遜一籌。<ref name="tg">{{en}}{{cite news|url=http://www.theguardian.com/film/2015/may/18/inside-out-review-cannes-film-festival-pixar|title=Inside Out review - a buoyant and sweet-natured comedy from Pixar|work=[[The_Guardian|The Guardian]]|author=Peter Bradshaw|date=2015-05-18|accessdate=2015-05-18|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150525021242/http://www.theguardian.com/film/2015/may/18/inside-out-review-cannes-film-festival-pixar|archivedate=2015-05-25}}</ref>《[[影音俱樂部|影音俱樂部]]》的伊格納特·維許奈維茲基（Ignatiy Vishnevetsky）雖對電影整體而言持正面評價，卻認為它「犧牲了皮克斯歷來的佳作中難以付諸言詞的優美和開疆拓土的覺察力，卻換來一部不停為了解釋而得配上旁白的電影」；此外，他也指出皮克斯的動畫師們應該在視覺設計上更具冒險精神，才得以匹配這部電影野心勃勃的構想。<ref>{{en}}{{Cite web|title = At Cannes, the latest from Pixar and a previous Palme D'Or winner|url = http://www.avclub.com/article/cannes-latest-pixar-and-previous-palme-dor-winner-219593|website = www.avclub.com|accessdate = 2015-11-17|deadurl = no|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20151118064815/http://www.avclub.com/article/cannes-latest-pixar-and-previous-palme-dor-winner-219593|archivedate = 2015-11-18}}</ref>

電影正式上映後，也持續獲得好評。《[[HitFix|HitFix]]》的克里斯多福·塔普利（Kristopher Tapley）不僅稱它是2015年的最佳電影，甚至是「21世紀最佳的電影之一」。<ref>{{en}}{{cite web|url=http://www.hitfix.com/in-contention/more-than-just-pixars-best-inside-out-is-a-new-animation-masterpiece|title=More than just Pixars best, Inside Out is a new animation masterpiece|date=2015-03-10|work=HitFix|accessdate=2016-03-04|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160228182537/http://www.hitfix.com/in-contention/more-than-just-pixars-best-inside-out-is-a-new-animation-masterpiece|archivedate=2016-02-28}}</ref><ref>{{en}}{{cite web|url=http://variety.com/2015/film/in-contention/2015-movie-superlatives-1201667834/|title=2015 Movie Superlatives - Variety|author=Kristopher Tapley|work=Variety|accessdate=2016-03-04|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304054645/http://variety.com/2015/film/in-contention/2015-movie-superlatives-1201667834/|archivedate=2016-03-04}}</ref>《[[纽约时报|紐約時報]]》的{{Tsl|en|A. O. Scott|A·O·史考特}}認為電影是個「十足的樂趣」，並特別讚賞它「替悲傷的辯護，在娛樂的華麗包裝下辯稱憂鬱乃是不可或缺的。」<ref name="nyt15">{{en}}{{cite news|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2015/06/19/movies/review-pixars-inside-out-finds-the-joy-in-sadness-and-vice-versa.html|title=Review: Pixar's 'Inside Out' Finds the Joy in Sadness, and Vice Versa|first=A. O.|last=Scott|date=2015-06-18|accessdate=2015-06-19|work=[[The_New_York_Times|The New York Times]]|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150619042914/http://www.nytimes.com/2015/06/19/movies/review-pixars-inside-out-finds-the-joy-in-sadness-and-vice-versa.html|archivedate=2015-06-19}}</ref>《[[华盛顿邮报|華盛頓郵報]]》的安·霍納迪（Ann Hornaday）則認為它是「一部超越純粹的娛樂、而成為某種讓人們的情感真正得到宣洩甚至療癒的罕見電影。它給予孩子們一套象徵性語言，以管理他們最難掌控的情緒。」<ref name="wp15">{{en}}{{cite news|url=http://www.washingtonpost.com/goingoutguide/movies/inside-out-mixes-adventure-and-brain-science-to-create-a-literal-joy-ride/2015/06/17/87e29df2-1450-11e5-9ddc-e3353542100c_story.html|title='Inside Out' mixes adventure and brain science to create a literal joy ride|first=Ann|last=Hornaday|date=2015-06-18|accessdate=2015-06-19|work=[[The_Washington_Post|The Washington Post]]|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150619224532/http://www.washingtonpost.com/goingoutguide/movies/inside-out-mixes-adventure-and-brain-science-to-create-a-literal-joy-ride/2015/06/17/87e29df2-1450-11e5-9ddc-e3353542100c_story.html|archivedate=2015-06-19}}</ref>《[[芝加哥太陽報|芝加哥太陽報]]》的{{Tsl|en|Richard Roeper|理察·魯珀}}認為電影「大膽、華麗、甜美、有趣，有時又傷感得令人心碎」，並稱它是2015年最佳的電影之一。<ref name="cst15">{{en}}{{cite news|url=http://entertainment.suntimes.com/movies/inside-funny-gorgeous-exploration-one-girls-brain/ |title=Inside Out: A Funny, Gorgeous Exploration of One Girl's Brain |author=Richard Roeper |date=2015-06-15 |accessdate=2015-06-19 |work=[[Chicago_Sun-Times|Chicago Sun-Times]] |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150618010802/http://entertainment.suntimes.com/movies/inside-funny-gorgeous-exploration-one-girls-brain/ |archivedate=2015-06-18 }}</ref>《[[娱乐周刊|娛樂周刊]]》的克里斯·納沙瓦西（Chris Nashawathy）認為電影「卓越且動人…在心理層面上極為高明」。<ref name="ew15">{{en}}{{cite news|url=http://www.ew.com/article/2015/06/16/inside-out-ew-review|title=Inside Out: EW review|author=Chris Nashawathy|date=2015-06-16|accessdate=2015-06-19|work=[[Entertainment_Weekly|Entertainment Weekly]]|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150618182904/http://www.ew.com/article/2015/06/16/inside-out-ew-review|archivedate=2015-06-18}}</ref>《[[時代_(雜誌)|時代雜誌]]》的瑪麗·波爾斯（Mary Pols）則認為電影「摒棄了家庭電影慣用的框架」而成為一部「近乎致幻、全然美麗」的佳作。<ref name="t15">{{en}}{{cite news|url=http://time.com/3925611/inside-out-pixar-movie-review/|title=Review: Inside Out Takes a Mind-Blowing Trip Inside the Brain|author=Mary Pols|date=2015-06-18|accessdate=2015-06-19|work=[[時代_(雜誌)|Time]]|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150618221401/http://time.com/3925611/inside-out-pixar-movie-review/|archivedate=2015-06-18}}</ref>《[[大西洋月刊|大西洋月刊]]》的{{Tsl|en|Christopher Orr (film critic)|克里斯多福·歐爾}}鼓勵讀者觀賞本片，並稱它「帶有那種面面俱到、感人肺腑的故事，而讓你很難想像它不是皮克斯的作品」，也「使皮克斯再度站上頂尖」。<ref name="atl15">{{en}}{{cite news|url=http://www.theatlantic.com/entertainment/archive/2015/06/inside-out-review-pixar/396311/|title=With Inside Out, Pixar Returns to Form|author=Christopher Orr|date=2015-06-19|accessdate=2015-06-19|work=[[大西洋月刊|The Atlantic]]|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150620074108/http://www.theatlantic.com/entertainment/archive/2015/06/inside-out-review-pixar/396311/|archivedate=2015-06-20}}</ref>《{{Tsl|en|Los Angeles Review of Books|洛杉磯書評}}》的{{Tsl|en|Wai Chee Dimock|宋慧慈}}則認為，電影的構想可與{{Tsl|en|Antonio Damasio|安東尼奧‧達馬西奧}}、{{Tsl|en|Dacher Keltner|達契爾‧克特納}}及[[奧利佛·薩克斯|奧利佛·薩克斯]]等神經學家的研究相提並論。<ref>{{en}}{{cite web|url=http://lareviewofbooks.org/essay/pixar-and-the-brain-scientists/|title=Pixar and the Brain Scientists|work=The Los Angeles Review of Books|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150713231055/http://lareviewofbooks.org/essay/pixar-and-the-brain-scientists/|archivedate=2015-07-13}}</ref>。

